  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

<a name="wp3679695"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
Description
</h3>    

<a name="wp3679696"> </a><p class="pBody" >
The <code class="cCodeBody">assert_never</code> assertion checker checks the single-bit expression <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> at each rising edge of <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">clk</span> to verify the expression does not evaluate to TRUE.
</p>    
<a name="wp3679705"> </a><h4 class="pHead4" >
Assertion Checks  </h4>    <div align="left" class="tbl">
<table border="0">
  <caption></caption>
  <tr align="left" valign="top">    <td><a name="wp3679700"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
&#160;
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3679702"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
ASSERT_NEVER
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3679704"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
Expression evaluated to TRUE.
</div>    
</td>
</tr>
  <tr align="left" valign="top">    <td><a name="wp3680088"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
&#160;
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3680090"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
test_expr contains X/Z value
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3680092"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
Expression evaluated to X or Z, and &#8216;OVL_XCHECK_OFF is not set.
</div>    
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
	
  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

<a name="wp3679706"> </a><h4 class="pHead4" >
Cover Points
</h4>    

<a name="wp3679707"> </a><p class="pBody" >
none
</p>    
<a name="wp3679708"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
Notes
</h3>    

<a name="wp3679709"> </a><p class="pNumber" >
 1.	By default, the <code class="cCodeBody">assert_never</code> assertion is pessimistic and the assertion fails if <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> is not 0 (i.e.equals 1, X, Z, etc.). However, if &#8216;OVL_XCHECK_OFF is set, the assertion fails if and only if <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> is 1.
</p>    
<a name="wp3680472"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
See also
</h3>    

<p class="pCodeShiftTop"></p><a name="wp3680473"> </a><pre class="pCode2" >assert_always, assert_always_on_edge, assert_implication, 
assert_proposition
</pre>    
